detailedDescription:
The algarve portugal sigtning was a clear ufo. i am using aviation phrases to describe conditions, i am flying for more than 15 years. 

object: 
no noise, no directional change, straight line path flying over the coastline on approx. track 270 magnetic course. the sun at the day in early september was shining bright conditions cavok. from the side where the sun lighted the object it was white and had a shape like a katana microplane (the school 2 seater) but was built up in 2 levels. on the backside there raged out a hockey stick like aileron which was not moving. 

position & ground speed: 
the object was flying direction west parrallel to the the eastwards right hand upwind of fao airport (the usual commercial outbound) routing. this means against the direction of commercial traffic and a bit above the route. the object was moving with appros 250 kts steadily. as i ran behind the next building to follow it up it was out of my sight at approx. 60 degrees angle from horizon directly over the city center of quarteira, portugal direction albufeira.

conclusion: 
we have a small house in the area which i am visiting since 25 years. in this time there i have never whitnessed such an object flying in the area. also there was sure no educated pilot in charge, because flying an object in a departure area of an intl. airport would be suicidal...
description: Object flown straight line overhead, approx. 8 miles from fao airport. i am a pilot therefore i know it wasnt an aircraft known by authorities. neither it was a commercial aircraft. i saw the object viewing the sky lying at the pool

detailedDescription: El pasado jueves 7 de agosto de 2014 en la localidad de la bañeza - león - españa, en torno a las 22:30 y 23:00 he sido espectador de un acontecimiento un tanto peculiar en mi vida, pues mientras me dirigía a dar un paseo y a fumar después de haber cenado me dirigía por un camino y al pasar el ultimo edificio percibí una luz en el cielo semejante a una estrella, en un primer momento pensé estar viendo la estación espacial internacional, pues no es la primera vez que me pega un susto. esta vez fue diferente, se desplazaba a gran velocidad y otras dos luces un poco por delante de esta (estas dos también eran semejantes a una estrella pero con una intensidad lumínica menor) se adentraron en una nube donde las perdí de vista por un segundo , cuando de repente una luz blanco-anaranjada salió del interior de esta. la primera luz de tambaleó un poco mientras aumentó su velocidad cruzando desde la parte  éste hasta noroeste pasando por delante de un avión comercial proveniente de león después  desapareciendo detrás de una nube. al poco momento una estrella fugaz apareció un poco mas al oeste de la posición del avión.Poco después la luz reapareció pero en sentido contrario pasando por delante del avion y perdiéndose en una nube de contaminación lumínica de un pueblo cercano. esta visión me produjo una sensación similar a la que me produce el asmr pero mucho mas intensa, con la piel de gallina, no quería quitar la vista de estas luces dado que era mi primera experiencia real en primera persona. al darme cuenta de que ya no vería mas me dirigí a mi casa a redactar al detalle lo que vi. pero yo creo que no lo olvidaré nunca.
description: La primera era una estrella de gran intensidad luminica las otras mas suaves

detailedDescription:
I was in a parked car with 2 friends in a yard on the suburbs. i was in the backseat listening the radio one saturday at 1 or 2 o'clock (am).
my 2 friends who were sitted in the front seats start to say... "what is that...Oh men...Whats that light!!!". i got up and looked trough the glass... and i saw it.
in front of us, at 3 or 4km starts a 700m mountain with a red light on his top, well, the ufo was 200 or 300meters above that light, it was like a "little sun" , a red-orange glowing ball wich made mad turnings at incredible speed, one time... it seemed to fall with gravity acceleration but stoped instantly and continued makin turns.From hovering,the ufo flew more than 20cms in our perspective in less than 1 second, who means more than 10km in real distance,braking instantly and making other 10perspective cms in the opossite way, it did random turns during 2 minutes.
at last, the ufo flew to our right (north direction) and we lose it, we get out from the car and ran to see it but we couldt target it no more.
i am a veteran soldier of the spanish army, i was in afghanistan and in a lot of exercises , i used ir devices and marked zones to helis and planes, i know how seems the ordinary airplanes ... and it wasnt a plane or heli, it had imposible acceleration and braking.One friend who was sitted in the front was soldier too in the spanish air force with beacon works in the airstrip and hangars and he was impressed like me.
we also know that the ufo wasnt above the mountain, we guess it was a lot of km behind the mountain at higer altitude, we were in getxo heading west so we guess the ufo was above cantabria, the neighbour province, we saw the ufo above the mountain cause the perspective...We guess.
description: A light over a mountain turning abruptily at high speeds with impossible braking and hovering.

detailedDescription:
wednesday afternoon, between 18.00 and 20.00, i was lying in a park here in logrono, basking in the sunlight. the air was clear; it was not too hot. not a cloud in sight. for a while i lay with my eyers closed. around 19.00 i opened my eyes and looked up in the sky. i looked at all the birds flying above me, the dust particles drifting around, the passenger airplanes passing to and from bilbao and simply enjoyed myself. the sun was shining directly on my head; i didn't see the sun when gazing straight upwards, it was just above my eyes. in other words, my view of the sky was as perfect as it gets that time of day here in logrono. then, a thought of ufos passed my mind, and in that second, a white dot materialized above me, far far up in the sky. it travelled in a straight line very very fast, but not too fast for my eyes too follow. it travelled in a straight line from north to south. since my sight had already been calibrated by the birds at different altitudes, airplanes and dust particles of different kinds, i could clearly see that it was not any of those things, that is birds, airplanes or dust particles. i could also clearly see that it was very high up in the sky, higher up than passenger airplanes travel. it also moved much faster than an average passenger airplane. in some seconds, it was gone on the southern horizon, due to the air getting 'thicker' towards the horizon. i was very calm, but i understood what i had just seen, even if it was hard to believe. some minutes passed, and i started to doubt my own perception and my interpretation of it, thinking it was probably just a bird or something. as soon as i had thought this, a new one appeared, at the same spot, travelling in the same direction at the same speed. now i noticed, while i was watching it, that as long as i was was actually observing it, there was no doubt whatsoever that this was not a bird, airplane or dust particle. also, i noticed that i was fully alert, registering as much as i possibly could, and not in any way 'shaken' by the sight. then it was gone. and then, in some minutes, came the doubt as to what i had seen. maybe it was a low flying satelite, reflecting the sun? again i was 'in limbo' concerning what i'd just seen. some minutes later, and a third one 'materialized' just above me, like the other two, travelling at the same speed (tremendous), altitude and trajectory. before it disappeared from sight, i thought 'why don't you make a turn, so i'll know you're not a satelite?' and at that very moment, it made a turn (to the west)!!! then it was out of sight. then a cessna plane or something of that kind came flying low over me, followed by a fourth ufo, same as the ones before. but before this one vanished over the horizon, a passenger airplane came along. their trajectories crossed, and now it was plain to see that the ufo was flying much higher, and much much faster than the passenger airplane. btw, the ufos were white dots, very small, yet very visible, but only for those looking intently up at the sky at the very place where they were flying. i would say they were circular, but that's hard to tell at such distance. they were, or seemed at any rate, very solid, white things, with no discernible shape. again, the ufo disappeared, and again the doubt came sneeking up on me. and then came another, and then another, until the doubt seemed more like vanity than anything scientifically substantial. all in all, i saw ten such ufos in the span of half an hour. i never saw two at the same time, but at one time a new one appeared immediately after the last one disappeared over the horizon, so i guess it must have been at least two, but probably ten, unless the same ufo flew over me until out of sight, and then teleported back to just above me, doing this ten times. one of the ufos had more of a west/east trajectory, the others more or less in a straight north/south trajectory.
after the ufos had passed, i noticed a small cloud, of the cummulus kind, with lots of creases and shapes, the type of cloud you see faces and stuff in, moving towards me from the south-east towards north-west. i was baffled by the speed at which it 'unfolded'; in a minute or two it had tripled or quadrupled it's size. it looked, visually that is, far more astonishing than the ufos. as it had dramatically increased it's size, it turned into a uniform foggy patch in a matter of seconds. it went from being your average type of cartoon-cummulus to an elongated circular patch of uniform 'fog' in probably no more than two minutes, expanding it's area by probably 600-1000% in that time span. the transformation happened just above me, where i'd seen the ufos 'materialize' earlier, but at much lower altitude, maybe a fifth of the altitude of the ufos, although that is only a guesstimation.
i believe i've answered point 1-3 above.
4: white dots, most probably circular. moved in straight trajectories from north to south at very high speeds, took maybe 10 seconds to cross the sky. one ufo made a turn towards the west, one ufo had a west-east trajectory. uniform speed, many times greater than an average passenger airplane.
5: calm, observing and accepting during observation, followed by disbelief, this was repeated ten times until it was no longer followed by disbelief. it seemed ordinary in a strange way.
6: i loosed sight of the objects as they moved closer to the horizon, where they disappeared in the more white light towards the horizon. i would say they disappeared from sight due to the angle through the atmosphere i was seeing them; as they got closer to the horizon they were obscured by the increasing amount of air/humidity/pollution through which i saw them.

i did not have a camera with me, and i would have needed some really expensive gear for the pictures to have been interesting at any rate, due to the speed and altitude at which they were flying.
description: In half an hour i saw 10 ufos flying above me in sequence, very high altitude, very fast, very small but very visible.

detailedDescription:
I was woken up this morning at approximately 7.30 by a child, and as i turned over in bed i looked out the window  -  there was a bright light coming through it. the window faces west, towards biarritz (about (25 miles away). i realised i was looking at a very bright star, possibly the brightest star i have ever seen.

then as i sat up (as i had never seen a star there before) i thought the object consisted of two very bright steady orange lights together. i then assumed it was a plane taking off eastwards (towards me) from biarritz airport (though i have never seen this before either).

the lights (or object) rose very slowly, and i assumed that it was indeed a plane, coming towards me after take-off.

slowly the lights started to move vertically upwards, and as they did so became fainter. within 10 seconds it had covered about 20 degrees of sky. within another 20 seconds it had covered another 30, all the while  growing fainter, indicating that it was moving further away  -  indeed, the lights or object diminished in size rapidly.

within another 10 seconds it was gone in what i assume was cloud, though it was too dark to see if that was the case. there was no rooster tail or trail, and no noise (though the window was closed. there were no flashing lights, or other colours in the object.

did someone execute a missile launch in the bay of biscay this morning -  that is almost the only scenario i can see replicating these conditions ?  i am assuming it was a natural phenomena, and apart from a great sense of wonder and curiosity i have no other feelings. my over-riding impression was that this was an object at great speed. as it ascended i had the impression it curved slightly to the left (southwestwards).

i have never seen a meteor or a piece of space debris move that fast or as shine as brightly.
description: Orange light ascending vertically at speed

detailedDescription:
Here's what just happened. i was in my house's balcony talking on the phone with a friend of mine, i usually go there at night, since i like to just relax in the dark listening to some music and look up at the sky. now, because i was on the phone, i wasn't paying too much attention to the sky and the few times i actually looked at it i couldn't see many stars due to the clarity of the moon this night. from where i was, i couldn't see the moon, my back was facing it plus, the roof of my house would cover it a bit, but still, the amount of light it reflected was enough to 'cover' some of the light of the starts in the sky.
anyway, at one point of the conversation, i looked at the sky and just focused my attention on the most radiant thing in the area i was looking at. i usually do this to figure out what am i looking at, is it a plane? is it a satellite? is it just a star? at first it looked like a star, its color was like any other, except it was moving. since there were no lights blinking it couldn't be a plane so i thought i was just lucky to 'pick' a satellite in the '1st try'.So i just moved onto the next light. and it was moving aswell. when i realised it, the 'stars' that i thought were in the area were actually not stars but rather some circular objects and were all flying next to each other in small groups in the same direction in a rather slow pace. their flight path was a straight line and they would assume triangular formations between them and it looked like there were some kind of light beams connecting one to another. i was narrating everything as it was happening on the phone to my friend and i just couldn't believe what i was seeing. i look up at the sky so many times looking for something and  there it was. something i couldn't explain. i just stood there watching for like 10 seconds. then i ran inside and called my sister to come and see but when she got there the lights were getting covered by the roof of our house and we lost sight of them. we went to the back of our house, but we didn't get to see them again. either they got away from there or, as i mentioned before, the amount of light reflected by the moon was intense enough to make these lights almost imperceptible.
description: Group of up to 10 star-looking objects moving together while beaming between them

detailedDescription:
(apologies if this sighting report was sent previously. i am unsure if the first report went through properly).

the photo was taken at 5:54 am on november 23, 2017, in madrid, spain. i was up early because of jetlag and was walking in the town. the photo was taken in the square of puerta del sol in the middle of madrid. i took the photo facing south from behind a statue (because it says "madrid" on it) and i was trying to get the shot of the statue with the frame of the christmas tree and the clock tower building.  it is possible that when i framed the shot the ufos were behind the christmas tree and only came into view (moved west) when i was busy making sure the clock tower building was in the shot.

at the time of the photo, i did not notice anything in the sky (i was not paying attention to the sky, as i did not think anything was there. also, there were several revelers in the area still partying from the night before, and making sure of my own safety i was keeping one eye on them and just quickly took the shot). my camera was just set to "automatic". it was only later the next day when i was going through my photos that i noticed the strange lights in the sky in the photo. at first i thought it was maybe just street lamps (as the street lamps in the area have either 4 or 2 lights on them) but even from the ufo photo i can see the lamps are much farther down. i then thought that maybe it was some odd reflection of the street lamps. however, i am outside and not in a store or restaurant (it was nearly 6 am at the time, and nothing is open at that time to my knowledge). although there is a christmas tree decoration, there is no glass there to reflect the street lamp lights. to check that it was not actually some kind of odd reflection, i went back the next day to take photos of the area. there is nothing in the sky to reflect the light from the lamps. there have never been photos of strange or odd things like this taken with this camera and lens before, so i can only conclude that it is a photo of ufos. thank you.
description: 4 objects in the sky spotted from within madrid, spain

detailedDescription: I was watching the clouds as i searched for airplanes and did my usual report of the chemtrails in my area, noticed a strange cloud and zoomed in with the mobile phone to try to see better but due to the bright sunlight could not see the screen and only after reviewing the images on the computer did i notice that i had in fact filmed something similar to other secret projects like the tr3b or sr91 aurora or similar. i send the original video, the link of my youtube page as well as copies in slow motion and some photos with filter applied. i'm not sure but i was left with the feeling that there are more objects next to the triangular object. you will have to analyze better.Good news and your answer.Carlos vieira.

detailedDescription: My second ufo experience in the city of toledo (spain). we returned from the celebration of the bonfire of san juan (party of the summer solstice in spain) and going by the known in the city as an ecological path, next to the tagus river, we looked up to the sky and saw a group of lights almost on our heads. we quickly realized that they could not be planes (no noise), or satellites (never fly so many together and it was late, so the sun could no longer reflect their rays in them), nor drones, nor chinese lanterns (because they were very fast and seemed to fly at high altitude), or anything that we knew. our reaction was one of great astonishment. they carried a movement of constant speed and rectilineal. when we looked up some had already passed near our zenith and others were coming, following the first. they were lost by the horizon, which marked a cliff by the river, so our view of the sky was not very wide.
description: Large group of white lights (about 30 objects or more), somewhat smaller than the international space station. they all flew in the same direction.

detailedDescription:
I was with a friend walking back to our houses after hanging out, it was at night (around 11 pm) and there were some fireworks going on at the time so we looked up to see them. but when i looked up i saw lots of distanced lights flashing (and i'm 100% sure it wasn't the fireworks since there was no explosions in that particular area of sky). at first i didn't think much of it (you know, could be planes and stars just shinning as usual) but the amount of flasheds in that particular area didn't feel normal. after a while i saw them moving slowly like flocks of birds. i counted around 10-15 (maybe more) "star-like" objects flashing very quickly - like christmas lights-, moving freely. i wasn't sure how to feel because i'm very skeptic about these kinds of deals because the usual reports are just some "dude" in the middle of the desert with a crappy camera and cut-off footage. but this time... i don't know. when my friend (who witnessed the event) went home the lights were still there, moving and blinking like no tomorrow, i believe at some point the conglomerate of lights made a cross (probably «just a coincidence but i'm just trying to be as descriptive as i can) but it just shows how much they were moving. after i took footage of the event i walked back home always looking to the sky to see what more could happen. the "lights" started to move further and further away until they dissipated into the darkness of the night sky. after i came home and showed my father the footage he was as skeptic as me and told me to send it to some site's like these. i completely forgot that i had the footage on my computer saved until now. this is all i can remember and describe.

hope there's some explanation to this. 


p.S the photos attached were taken one after the other and in one of the videos my friend says "are we high or something? (just to clear things up).

hope there's some explanation to this.
description: Cluster of lights in the air (almost like stars)

detailedDescription:
Olá
o meu avistamento passa-se em portugal nos arredores da cidade do porto numa vila que hoje também é cidade, chamada maia entre 1978 1979,  não sei precisar ao certo. eu teria na altura unss 10 anos mais ao menos.
nessa época eu vivia numa zona um pouco rural e meia deserta. minha casa ficava a 2 km da casa mais próxima e se situada entre um grande campo de cultivo na frente da casa e uma bouça nas traseiras. o sitio era muito fixe mas de noite metia um pouco de medo. tudo isto se passa depois do jantar, como não tínhamos casa de banho dentro de casa e a casa de banho ficava nas traseiras da casa e não tinha luz era uma vela que usavam os eu pedi a minha mãe para vir fazer xixi em frente à casa,  como tínhamos uma lâmpada logo a saída da porta eu podia estar sossegado. liguei a luz e disse a minha mãe que  estava na cozinha a lavar a loiça que ia fazer xixi... sai e quando estava de costas para a casa e virado para o campo ouvi um zumbido não muito fraquinho quando me volto fico perplexo com o que vejo a pairar por cima da minha casa, um objecto com cerca de três metros de diâmetro em forma de disco prateado e cheio de luzinhas brilhantes, ainda chamei a minha mãe para ela vir ver mas ela não ligou nenhuma. o objecto 2 ou 3 minutos mais como se me estivesse a observar e depois ganhou um velocidade incrível e desapareceu em dois segundos  nas estrelas .No dia seguinte como o meu pai trazia o jornal todos os dias depois do trabalho e como morava relativamente perto do aeroporto francisco sá carneiro, tentei ver se havia alguma notícia a falar de alguma coisa, mas não apareceu nada. na altura não tive medo mas passei a ver o mundo de outra forma e foi sempre acompanhado o que se vai passando pelo nosso planeta. durante o tempo que vivi nessa casa nunca mais voltei a ter outro avistamento, mas tive várias situações de me deitar na sala e acordar no quarto sem saber como e não sou sonâmbulo, mas também não sei se isso tem alguma relação. mas a melhor está para vir. hoje em dia tenho uma filha com 22 anos e o namorado dela aconteu-lhe uma coisa bastante estranha. a pouco tempo ele acordou de manhã com um golpe na cabeça perto da fonte, pegou e foi ao hospital ver o que era aquilo porque não se lembra de fazer esse golpe. conclusão os médicos no hospital disseram a ele que ele não podia estar vivo e não têem explicação. obrigado por poder partilhar a minha história. lf
description: Objectivo em forma de disco prateado e cheio de luzes

detailedDescription: It was mid august 2013. got up around 4am(gmt) and made myself a cup of coffee and went to my rear (eastern) balcony, looked up, the sun was already rising over the mountains, and that's when i saw it, a translucent chrome sphere. it moved very slowly, didn't make a sound, what i actually noticed was the absence of ambient sound. no noises, no car sounds, no bird chirps, no wind noise, and it was a bit windy. it probably hovered at an altitude of 30/40 meters, and from 500 to 700 meters in front of me, moved in various directions for about 20 minutes, during that time, it gradually started to "build up" a misty cloud on the lower part of the sphere, then absorbed through the misty part two other smaller spheres that appeared similar in nature, at that point it changed to an oval shape that was tilted to the side, oscilated quite a bit and clearly rotated on itself. the rest of the time, it "built up" even more mist, to the point when it appeared thicker than a cloud, after that, heading in a ne direction, it disappeared leaving a small trail and a pale blue/greenish hue. at the time, i thought it was a beautiful event, very soothing. but i saw it again today, and i live 200 kilometres away from that other location, and where i live now is considered to be a very ufo activite area, since it's close to the sea.
flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change
description: I woke up at 4am, around 5 i was standing on my rear balcony smoking a cigarette, when suddenly i noticed a sphere in the sky, it was solid, unlike a bubble, simultaneously chrome and translucent. hovered for a while, then disappeared leaving thick mist.

detailedDescription:

detailedDescription:
I was sitting in my couch, in my living room attempting contact through the ce-5 process. when i initiated the meditation process (that i had never attempted before), i felt a slight pressure in the center of my forehead about the size of a coin. soon that pressure extended to my chest and stomach, all three seemingly vibrating in unison. 

after a while, i started visualizing something - silhouettes of bodies. i remember three in particular. one seemed just like us, only taller and wider shoulders, the others seemed like what we call "greys" and the last seemed weirder, "insectoid-like" beings. the only way i can explain this is that it felt the exact same as if when downloading an image on an internet browser, you select "always open after download". i felt completely safe and peaceful, as if i was being shown a family album filed with beings that i had never seen. 

upon finishing the meditation, i got up and went to my window, waiting to see if my attempt at establishing contact had received a reply. during this time i was wondering if all that i had seen was just the product of my imagination, inspiring itself on our expectations on how an alien would look like. 

a few minutes had passed and i was looking at my right side, when suddenly i felt the same pressure on my forehead and an urge to look towards my left. to my surprise, hovering over the mountain behind my house, there were two white orbs. one pulsed, the other blinked. 

i stood there, completely stunned, frozen in place. my mind rushed through the possibilities. planes don't hover, helicopters make noise (and there was no noise at all), cars don't float and nothing that i know can hover, blink and pulse light and be the size of a golf ball at that distance. in all the years i've lived here, i've never seen any lights like that in that location or anywhere, for that matter. 

i was slowly reaching the conclusion that there was no other explanation and so, i thought - "is it really you?" - and instantly, the orbs started blinking/pulsing at a much faster rate. needless to say that when this happened, i simply stood there in awe over what i was witnessing. i do not want to reach conclusions but i would be lying if i didn't say that it felt that they had not just responded to my contact attempt but that also, they were giving me an answer to a question that i did not verbalize, but rather thought. 

as far as the orbs, they simply disappeared as inexplicably as they appeared. after they left, i believe that i stood in front of my window for another five minutes or more, trying to make sense of what had just happened.

at no point during my meditation or visualization of the orbs did i ever feel threatened, afraid or did i see anything that would justify that i would feel that way.
description: Attempted contact through ce-5 - two hovering orbs appear above the mountain behind my house

detailedDescription:
Me encontraba observando con mi telescopio en las siguientes coordenada sobre las 22:30 tiempo oficial aproximadamente en las coordenadas 39âº 55' n    0âº 37' w en el municipio de viver a unos 700m de altura. la noche era clara en un 4 sobre 5 de seing por lo que la magnitud que se podia alcanzar visualmente de las estrellas a ojo desnudo rondaba la 6âª.
aparecio una luz muy brillante hacia el sur-sureste completamente estatica de color amarillo anaranjado con un fuerte destello vibratorio de intensidad variable pero leve. se mantuvo estã¡tica a una altura de unos 20âº por encima de mi horizonte que yo estimo que seria de otros 15 o 20 por lo que no alcanzaria una altitud de 45âº con toda seguridad. ni el tipo de luz ni la posiciã³n me confirmaban que fuera un avion o helicoptero. estuvo estatica un minuto o dos y comenzo a desplazarse hacia el oeste al principio lentamente y luego con mas velocidad disminuyendo su brillo hasta desaparecer. estimo que recorreria un cuarto de hora de arco hasta desaparecer.
ni que decirle que jamas habia observado semejante cosa, por supuesto no era un dron, he visto varios y era imposible que la distancia que se encontraba, que luego pude mas o menos determinar, pudiera emitir esa luz.
en pleno estado de estupefaccion y anotando los datos que le relato, habrian trascurrido unos 10 minutos del cese de la aparicion, volviã³ a aparecer de manera instantanea en el mismo lugar del horizonte y a la misma altura. no hubo ningãºn punto de luz que fuera incrementandose sino que fue un subito resplandor con la misma intensidad que la primera vez.
en esta segunda ocasion se mantuvo estatico unos pocos segundos, tal vez 30 o 40 y comenzã³ de nuevo a moverse hacia el oeste pero esta vez se fue trasladando a mucha mas distancia. observe claramente que se desplazaba con velocidad claramente no uniforme, intercalaba movimientos largos rapidos con otros cortos mas lentos y ello daba la sensacion de que era segmentado. al mismo tiempo variaba la intensidad de la luz llegando en un momento a incrementar tanto la misma que pense que pudiera dirigirse hacia mi posicion.
este segundo avistamiento duro unos tres o cuatro minutos y debido a los cambios de luminosidad constantes quede totalmente confundido en estimar la distancia a la que podria encontrarse ya que bien podia ser un objeto pequeã±o cercano o grande lejano.
mis dudas se aclararon un poco cuando comenzo a descender ya sobrepasada la posicion sur- suroeste y comprobe que quedaba ocultado tras la sierra. el perfil de la sierra siempre fue claramente observable pues al encontrase tras ella la ciudad de valencia su alumbrado nocturno hace que sea perfectamente distinguible al recortarse ante ella.
estimo por todo ello que debio ocultarse de mi vista a unos 10 o 12 km de mi posicion por las coordenadas 39âº 48' n.  0â° 38' w y que su aparicion fue en torno a 39â° 53'n  0â°35' w habiendo estado a una distancia de unos tres o cuatro km de mi posicion y a una altura estimada de unos 1000-1200 m sobre el nivel del mar y a unos 300-400 sobre el suelo.
para terminar solamente insistir en que no he encontrado explicacion alguna a este avistamiento y por ello se lo comunico.
description: Luz anaranjada muy brillante.Estatica y con movimientos irregulares con dos apariciones sucesivas

detailedDescription:
So, this day, i smoking cigarettes outside. i'm used to do it looking at the stars. i have a certain knowledge of the normal position of the star and the planets and always look for venus or orion's belt, and normaly, i know before looking for it more or less where it should be.

this particular night when i look first glance at the sky, i see venus out of ambitual site. when i try to look venus where it should be, he certainly was there. so it was not venus. when a come back to see this object, i realize the object is moving, so a belief to be a satellite or the iss.

i keep track of the object and realize is not moving in linear and  change the inicial nw to sw derection to w. when i start to trying figured out what it is, the object make a total stoppage and stay like a minute in the same spot. 

i began to feel afraid, because there is not anything that can go to that height  suddenly  stop . after that 1 min,  stoped in the same spot, the object become brighter and disappear.

object it always the same size, and same bright of venus. only in the end become brighter and orange like color before disappear. in addition to this, it's important mention the " serra da estrela" ( the most elevated place in mainland portugal ) it's right behind me, and the object appear to come moving from there.

i stay with the feeling that the object stopped and disappeared, somehow realize i was watching it. i am very sceptical, and a never share this with no one, but haunts me down not know what i see that night. ( sorry my lousy english)

detailedDescription: I was driving and i sow some lights between the trees. i thought they were some kind of christmas lights though pretty big for that. as the car moved i realized there were more of them and when i turn the curb it was clear that they were in the middle of the sky  but  it was overcast and they appear and desappear probably due to the moving clouds. three of the lights were smaller or were higher and were separate from the rest of the group formed by around seven lights. this group keep a constellation kind of shape. i stop the car to see if they were making any noise like a helicopter but there was total silence. they stay like that for a few minutes. i was trying to take a picture with my cell phone but the streets lights were too bright and nothing came out. then, some of the lights starting to move, two of them may have fussed but i am not sure. them they disappear probably they went higher than the clouds.

detailedDescription: El pasado 30 de marzo del presente año 2015 circulaba con mi coche por una autovía de circunvalación, va30, que rodea la ciudad de valladolid (españa) sobre las 21:25 horas. al pasar junto  a la población de santovenia de pisuerga (pueblo muy cercano a la capital) observé unas "luces" sobre un polígono industrial que en un principio me parecieron luces de un estadio deportivo por su intensidad. a medida que me iba acercando veía con más claridad que no se trataba de ningún foco sino de toberas de cohete que desprendían una llama blanca y azul muy intensa y que pertenecían a un objeto que literalmente estaba flotando sobre el tejado de una nave industrial. boquiabierto y preguntándome constantemente ¿que era eso? lo dejé atrás a mi derecha no acabándome de creer lo que había visto. lo pierdo de vista y no volviendo más la vista atrás para evitar el accidente, continuo en marcha cuando a unos 400 metros aprox. más adelante el objeto volador se sitúa a mi derecha, a unos 100 metros de distancia y es cuando tengo el reflejo de coger mi teléfono móvil para fotografiarlo y cuando le hago las tres fotos que verán a continuación. también grabé con anterioridad a las fotos un video pero por la baja calidad del teléfono y la luz ambiente salió todo en negro, lamentablemente no se veía absolutamente nada. he de añadir que no hacía ningún tipo de ruido, tenía aproximadamente entre 12 y 15 metros de envergadura y podía mantenerse estático en el aire cosa que no he visto nunca en ningún aparato volador conocido que no sea un helicóptero o un avión de guerra tipo "caza", cosa que con toda seguridad no era. por último solo apuntar que si que reduje la velocidad pero no pensé en ningún momento en parar ya que circulaba por una autovía, venía otro vehículo detrás mio a unos 300 o 400 metros y no me hubiese gustado provocar un accidente.
description: Tenia la forma de un croissant alargado
locationName: Santovenia de Pisuerga, Castilla y León

when i looked up (almost in front) i saw a bright, shinning and big falling star...But it didn't disappeared. so i thought it was just an airplane flying low...But it didn't had lights (we usually see the reds lights blinking).
so i called my boyfriend so he could watch and see what was it.
between all of this i had time to pick up my camera in the living room and take some photos (i regret that i didn't made a video).
the object just flight straight, no strange moves, in a normal velocity, not slow, not fast...Blinked like a falling star (white shinning) and then it disappeared. started to loose shine and was gone.

detailedDescription:
1. i was taking a night walk with my husband in monsanto village, in portugal.

2. the village is located in an elevation and from there we have panoramic view for all the surrounding places, and i was facing east from a descending street in the same direction.

3. 'there goes an ufo'.

4. it was around 22.40pm. the sky was full of stars because there are few city and village lights interfering with the sky viewing, no clouds that night, summer breeze and 24c/75f of temperature. it was green light, round shaped, it looked like a green traffic light because of it's color and brightness. it was going in a fast speed from west to east, spain direction. the object only took 2 seconds covering a distance that a plane covers in about 20 seconds. it was probably more than 1 mile high, and at least 2 miles away from the place i was.

5. since it wasn't the first time i saw an ufo, i knew what i was seeing in that very same moment. i sometimes 'know' that something is going to happen a few minutes or hours before it happens, and sometimes 'something' makes me look up, like someone is tapping me in the shoulder and saying to me: 'look up, now'.
after the sighting i went to a terrace in the place i was staying, that has a panoramic view from the village surroundings and an incredidle sky visibility, stayed there for 40mn searching the sky but had no luck. the night after i spent 3h looking the sky between 9pm and 0am, but had no luck in a new sighting.

6. i was gone in a blink, like it was vanished in the air.
description: Green light ufo

detailedDescription: I was walking with several other people, checking out cuenca (town), which is located in ecuador. this was after dinner, so at night time. i looked up and saw a bright orange object in the night sky, and pointed it out to the others. we couldn't figure out what it was. it was just hovering there. it didn't appear to be a tower, as it was not connected to anything, and it was right above us. nor did it appear to be a flare (no fireworks then). it was completely silent and just hovering there. we watched it for a couple of minutes. then we just went about our business exploring the town.
description: Saw an orange object hovering in the night sky, while walking around in cuenca (town), ecuador.

detailedDescription:

eu costumo ver o vosso programa e vosso programa releva informações muito importantes para a humanidade, mas ela parece não ligar isso. obrigado pelo o fazem.

detailedDescription:
Every day we see ufos of all kinds in our skies . we have many photos and movies (i'm always looking at the sky , day or night. ) my husband and i went to play snooker, across the street where we left the car . when i left the car i look at the sky and all the sky moves . passed a constellation to another constellation and then the lights showed a triangle and a square faziem and when passed under we could see everything ... many flashing lights aleatory , with kind of appendages on the type of crane. with a straight path slowly from the mountains towards the sea. light red sentry was large in relation to the other guards . the distance from the ship was flying and some below. all quiet , no sound . my husband could not take his eyes off the ship and i was trying to take some pictures . during the sighting is a group of people almost beside us , but ignored any presence . a month later i had contact with a girl who told the same story , same day and time , but she was at a higher point, then us. looked at you tube that day that published the same type of ship, size color , lights with sentries on august 25 in the us. the object we saw for sure that it was not remotely and was full of occupants.
the end, we weren't to play snooker, we went right home...


https://www.Youtube.Com/watch?V=hkzd00mnmlq&noredirect=1

detailedDescription:
I am using my nightvision regularly during the nights in arosa, switzerland to watch the sky. i just let the videorecorder run and check in the morning the footage. usually i see a lot of airplanes but sometimes also round flying lights which might be satellites but they have various speed and on this video you can see two blinking stationary lights. this short video is the result of 15 hours video recording during the 5. and 7. january 2015 in arosa, switzerland. unfortunately my nightvision can only cover a small part of the sky and it would be helpful to watch and record the nightsky in a more structured manner because these walking and blinkings lights can be observed during every night. 
you will first see two flying lights, then an airplane for comparison reason and then two blinking stationary lights.
description: First two ights unknown, third light is an airplane for comparison reason, last two lights are stationary.

detailedDescription:
My children called out to me to check out a strange light in the night sky, passing by our home at some distance over the ocean. i saw a rather little and wobbling, rather slow moving light, heading in ne direction which is very unusual around here, as it also moved at a relatively low altitude. i managed to take just 1 picture as the light suddenly disappeared.

i was very surprised as i checked out the picture (zooming in), to see a kind of light track produced by the light due to the shutter speed of 0,8 sec, which also showed a circular, disc-shaped object, seemingly moving in a more or less erratic way, changing position all the way through.

hope this picture can shed some light on aero dynamical behavior of ufo's.

ps. f/5.6, iso 6400, fd 35 mm;
description: It flew by at some distance (over the ocean) and i just managed to take one picture

detailedDescription:

i open the window, light a cigarette and take a smoke. when i wanted to get the smoke out i put my head oustide the window an realize that the moon was on my right side; on south side. it was fullmoon that night.

i looked again in front of me, and the other light was still there on the same position, not moving.

i observe this phenomenon for about a few minutes, aproximately 5 minutes. the light was just there, very intense because it seems to be very far away, probably more than 5 miles. it was discribing a perfect circle on the nigth sky, not moving, on the top of the mountains.

i sweetch looking at the strange light and the moon a few times, just to be sure of what i was looking.

then, in a blinking of an eye, it just desapear.

algunas personas de lleida, creemos que puede ser un ovni, y el temblor ser causado por un impacto o despegue de la nave.

pero ninguna noticia habla de ovnis, solo de terremotos y seismos.

yo no me sorprend'' porque ya es la 3'' vez que veo esferas en el cielo con las mismas caracter''sticas. una vez en la misma ciudad un a''o atr''s viendo con mi pareja al medio d''a 2 esferas. otra vez en benicarl'' (castell''n) con mi ex novia, una esfera de color irisado metalizado de unos 3 o 4 metros de di''metro a unos 18 metros encima de mi cabeza y est''tica durante unos 15 segundos y en el centro del pueblo y tambi''n al mediod''a, esto ya en el a''o 2004.

los cuatro ya est''''''''''''''''''bamos at''''''''''''''''''nitos cuando el objeto iba perdiendo altura y justo dejamos de verlo por el tejado del chalet contiguo a si que decidimos salir a la calle ya que dos chalets m''''''''''''''''''s all'''''''''''''''''' del que nos encontr''''''''''''''''''bamos y en direcci''''''''''''''''''n al objeto hay solo campo, pero cuando llegamos la luz hab''''''''''''''''''a desaparecido, volvimos al chalet y cogimos el coche para acercarnos m''''''''''''''''''s por los caminos hacia donde hab''''''''''''''''''amos visto el objeto, pero nada, este no volvi'''''''''''''''''' a aparecer, lo hab''''''''''''''''''amos visto durante 30-35 segundos nada m''''''''''''''''''s.
durante las dos horas siguientes continuamos hablando sobre lo sucedido e intentado dar alguna explicaci''''''''''''''''''n cient''''''''''''''''''fica, pero llegamos a la conclusi''''''''''''''''''n de que eso no era ni un avi''''''''''''''''''n ni ning''''''''''''''''''n meteorito ni nada que hubi''''''''''''''''''ramos visto en otra ocasi''''''''''''''''''n, ya que eso no era humano, los haces de luz que parec''''''''''''''''''an lasers nos daban esa evidencia; parec''''''''''''''''''a como si este objeto estuviera escaneando algo o escaneando a la poblaci''''''''''''''''''n, como tecnolog''''''''''''''''''a muy avanzada que nos daba a pensar que eso fruto de algunos seres extraterrestres.
los 4 a d''''''''''''''''''a de hoy seguimos impresionados por lo que vimos y coment''''''''''''''''''ndoselo    a familiares y amigos algunos nos creen y otros nos llaman locos, pero esta claro que lo que vimos no fue imaginaci''''''''''''''''''n si no, para m'''''''''''''''''', el mayor avistamiento que he vivido y es algo que nunca nadie me va a poder negar.

from the time we begin to see other errant objects, much like stars in the sky, and moving very strangely. my friends and i discard the idea that it was a plane, a helicopter or a satellite. it was definitely a ufo. after a while, my boyfriend and his friend went for a walk around the area. were approximately 3am. they went back to see a very similar object.
it was something very like a star. the distance to the object was great. he was very tall and was flashing like any astral object.

detailedDescription: At 7am this morning while daylight was just breaking, my self and my partner both witnessed a very bright object which appeared to be descending towards the north east towards the coast. it just suddenly appeared in the middle of the sky and it's shape resembled the space station, which we see regularly.  however,  it was many times larger than the space station, faster and much brighter. there was no sound. after a few seconds the object  'merged' into a soft inverted triangular shape and then into a very bright globe shape.  it seemed to remain still whilst this happened.  the brightness softened as it moved away more slowly diagonally descending behind a mountain towards the coast.  during this time a cloud gradually formed around the object and by the time it disappeared from view it looked just like a small cloud, except that it was moving. can i just not that this was very much lower in the sky than the space station, which we have both seen many times. i did have the foresight to attempt to video this on my camera. the video did not register and the only audio is our voices. also the cloud that formed appeared to be in front of the object with the object towards the rear of the cloud.
description: Very large ( compared to the space station ) brighter and faster heading ne towards the coast and seemed to be descending.

detailedDescription:
My wife, my son (7 years old at that time) and i were on the beach in denia (38â°51'02.3"n 0â°05'59.5"e) having a relaxing afternoon while on holidays, when at around 17:30, my wife noticed on her right-hand side, a bright object cruising slowly just around above the castle of denia (38â°50'50.6"n 0â°06'49.0"e) towards our position, following the coastline in a south-east north-west path (38â°53'53.9"n 0â°03'54.0"e). in the beginning, we thought it was just a drone, but the object seemed too big and too bright from the distance to be just a drone, despite the sun could well reflect on metallic objects depending on the angle and position.  as the object was approaching, the brightness didn't seem to change but rather pulsate, which we started to think about something unusual. a commercial flight was around at that time but it was at a much further and a higher altitude and didn't interfere in any way with the object. i decided to get my phone and record it. i was a bit frustrated because in previous years i bring my camcorder with me for holidays and i like to record events and fun times. that particular year i decided not to get the camcorder and rely on solely on my smartphone. with the camcorder, i could have used the powerful optical zoom and better quality image to record the event.

the object was travelling on a steady speed and steady path position (the object didn't move on the sky up and down, it was me trying to steady my phone). i estimate the object was travelling in between 100-200 miles/h and an altitude of around 3000 feet or possibly less, with an angle with respect of the horizon of around 35 degrees.

the object seemed to be pulsating and was really quickly intermittently disappearing and appearing with black shades in contrast with its brightness.  

as the sky was so clear cloudless, there is no appreciation of the object moving. only at 2:21 in the video, i did a quick shot of the beach as a point of reference because i didn't want to lose track of it.

it took my attention that while we were on the beach, no one noticed anything or no one noticed that we were very excited looking and filming this object in the sky like they weren't aware that we were there. there was a couple just sitting 4 meters in front of us, facing nearly our direction and they didn't seem to care about our excitement or our finding in the sky....  they didn't even bother to look at what was going on in the sky... weird! in fact, no one on the beach, and there were quite a few people, seemed to notice the strange event. 

we believe we sighted a very good case of an unknown object of unknown origin but you can prove us wrong of course.

the object seemed to be flickering even more as it was disappearing in the distance towards valencia. at one point we couldn't see it anymore. 

the whole event lasted about 4 to 5 minutes.
description: Unknown orb/light object travelling at steady speed along the coast of denia, spain

detailedDescription:
Alrededor del mes de agosto, una de las noches estrelladas decidí apartarme de las luces y observar el cielo y las estrellas ya que en ese momento me fascinaba la astronomia. cuando llegue a un sitio lo suficientemente oscuro, pare y mire hacia arriba con una inclinacion de alrededor de unos 80º. pude observar una noche estrellada donde se podia distinguir con facilidad constelaciones, planetas... he de recalcar que en ese lugar desde un principio pude notar algo distinto en el ambiente, algo parecido a un microclima, no corria viento y el ambiente se sentia denso. note un escalofrio por todo mi cuerpo, esto provoco una reaccion involuntaria de mirar hacia arriba. en ese momento observe una formacion constituida por un total de 8 luces, se distribuian de forma que 3 de esas estrellas se sitiuaban en la zona superior, las otras 3 en la zona inferior y cada una de las luces restantes se encontraban en los dos extremos.

                                                .            .            .
   
                                      .                                             .

                                                .            .             .

esa es la forma del objeto, en su interior no se observaba ninguna luz, sin embargo, conforme pasaba por delante de las estrellas iba tapandolas, por lo que llego a la conclusion de que se trata de un o.V.N.I este objeto poseia una medida de aproximadamente dos campos de futbol, se desplazaba a baja velocidad y baja altitud, además no producia ningun sonido. senti de nuevo otro escalofrío, mire hacia atrás para ver si había alguien mirando. cuando volvi a ver el objeto este se encontraba en el horizonte de mi parte derecha, de pronto desaparacio a gran velocidad.
description: Observe el cielo estrellado y pude observar una formación de luces 3 arriba, 3 abajo, 1 delante y 1 detras, no hacia ruido y era de un tamaño alrededor de dos campos de futbol. tapaba todo el cielo estrellado. desaparecio en el horizonte a gran velocidad

detailedDescription: I was stargazing from my kitchen window at around 2:30am when i saw this dark thing in the sky that looked like it was moving. it was far away and it was dark and it was hard to see though, it was basically just what looked like a black object against a patch of dark sky so it was hard to tell what exactly i was looking at. i kept looking and it seemed to be moving in my direction, not super fast but also not super slowly, at a constant speed. in just a matter of seconds it was close enough for me to be able to make out its shape / color / details / etc. it was basically a black (maybe dark gray?) rectangular craft with a row of dim red lights that went all the way around it, and although i’m not entirely sure i think it also had some windows. it was flying pretty low so i could very clearly see it wasn't a plane/helicopter or anything like that, and it also made no sound as far as i can remember.
description: Silent rectangular craft flew over my neighborhood

detailedDescription:
Outside sunbathing. daughter pointed it out. i considered was it a ballon, a helicopter then i said it must be a drone. it was very low, so thought most obvious. but when i stood on rocks to be higher it was not like a drone. it moved like a drone perhaps, backwards forwards, circular. the shape was strange, difficult to describe, rounded but with angles, it was longish, very black like a crow. then it was just there not really moving, we kep5 watching, then we started waving and it went off to the left climbing very high and there was like a gas almost surrounding it, but invisible, if that makes sense.
it was daytime, no clouds, hot. we watched for about 7 mins then it moved very quickly after my daughter and i waved a lot and i kept my eye on it as it was very strange, almos5 magical, as i watched it vanished in front of our eyes, no obstruction, just poof and it was gone,
we are in spain, murcia. i didn’t think to record it as i was mesmerised by it, i will try if i ever see it again, whatever it was!

detailedDescription: My second ufo experience in the city of toledo (spain). we returned from the celebration of the bonfire of san juan (party of the summer solstice in spain) and going by the known in the city as an ecological path, next to the tagus river, we looked up to the sky and saw a group of lights almost on our heads. we quickly realized that they could not be planes (no noise), or satellites (never fly so many together and it was late, so the sun could no longer reflect their rays in them), nor drones, nor chinese lanterns (because they were very fast and seemed to fly at high altitude), or anything that we knew. our reaction was one of great astonishment. they carried a movement of constant speed and rectilineal. when we looked up some had already passed near our zenith and others were coming, following the first. they were lost by the horizon, which marked a cliff by the river, so our view of the sky was not very wide.
description: Large group of white lights (about 30 objects or more), somewhat smaller than the international space station. they all flew in the same direction.

detailedDescription:
I was in the kitchen, waiting for the dinner to be ready, when i walked to the balcony and looked to the sky right in front (like i usually do, since i like to watch the sky/stars/moon and i'm always looking for some falling star, beautiful moon...)
when i looked up (almost in front) i saw a bright, shinning and big falling star...But it didn't disappeared. so i thought it was just an airplane flying low...But it didn't had lights (we usually see the reds lights blinking).
so i called my boyfriend so he could watch and see what was it.
between all of this i had time to pick up my camera in the living room and take some photos (i regret that i didn't made a video).
the object just flight straight, no strange moves, in a normal velocity, not slow, not fast...Blinked like a falling star (white shinning) and then it disappeared. started to loose shine and was gone.

detailedDescription:
Me encontraba en el jardin trasero de casa de mis padres junto a la piscina en dos tumbonas hablando con un amigo, la hora era las 12,40 aproximadamente, principios de agosto de 1992. en un momento de la conversacion en la que nos estabamos mirando hubo un flash potentisimo,  de luz muy blanca que ilumino todo lo que me rodeaba dandole al contorno de las cosas matices azulados, como el flash de una camara de fotos pero muchisimo mas potente y de luz mas blanca, esa luz vino de encima de nosotros y al mirar hacia arriba vimos una estrella fugaz que se dirigia al oeste y tres luces que formaban un triangulo equilatero.

las luces de ese triangulo equilatero eran de color anaranjado, de luz fija, muy visibles pero sin ser brillantes y muy grandes con respecto a las de un avion de pasajeros.

si las comparo, diria que las luces de un avion de pasajeros son como una pelota de ping pong y las 3 luces serian como las de una pelota de baloncesto. la altura a la que a mi me dio la impresion que estaba, es la de un avion de pasajeros y su velocidad era lenta, algomas lenta que cuando vemos pasar un avion a gran altura.
iba en linea recta y deje de verlo cuando el cipres de la casa vecian me tapo la vision , me levante rapidamente e intemte seguir viendolo pero los arboles no me dejaron ver y para cuando corri a la parte delantera de casa de mis padres habia desaparecido.

intente asegurarme de lo que habia visto y de que no me estaba equivocando y me fije en las ventanas de la casa de los vecinos que estaban cerradas por si el fogonazo podia ser una camara, pero no habia nadie y nunca habia visto un flash tan potente, no habia nadie ni se oia nada.

mi amigo se quedo sorprendido, pero cuando lo conte al resto de mis amigos el no dijo nada , no lo nego pero no ha querido volver a hablar de lo ocurrido.

esto ocurrio en una parte de la ciudad un tanto apartada, pero muy cercana y esa luz tuvo que verla alguien mas , a no ser que iluminase solo las parcelas mia y de mi vecino.

escribo esto porque en uno de vuestros programas de television se decribio un objeto con las mismas caracteristicas al que vi y quisiera saber si he tenido algun error de percepcion o tiene alguna explicacion logica.
description: Flash de luz que ilumina todo lo que me rodea, con luz blanca azulada y en el cielo 3 luces fijas anaranjadas en triangulo aquilatero

detailedDescription:
1. i was taking a night walk with my husband in monsanto village, in portugal.

2. the village is located in an elevation and from there we have panoramic view for all the surrounding places, and i was facing east from a descending street in the same direction.

3. 'there goes an ufo'.

4. it was around 22.40pm. the sky was full of stars because there are few city and village lights interfering with the sky viewing, no clouds that night, summer breeze and 24c/75f of temperature. it was green light, round shaped, it looked like a green traffic light because of it's color and brightness. it was going in a fast speed from west to east, spain direction. the object only took 2 seconds covering a distance that a plane covers in about 20 seconds. it was probably more than 1 mile high, and at least 2 miles away from the place i was.

5. since it wasn't the first time i saw an ufo, i knew what i was seeing in that very same moment. i sometimes 'know' that something is going to happen a few minutes or hours before it happens, and sometimes 'something' makes me look up, like someone is tapping me in the shoulder and saying to me: 'look up, now'.
after the sighting i went to a terrace in the place i was staying, that has a panoramic view from the village surroundings and an incredidle sky visibility, stayed there for 40mn searching the sky but had no luck. the night after i spent 3h looking the sky between 9pm and 0am, but had no luck in a new sighting.

6. i was gone in a blink, like it was vanished in the air.
description: Green light ufo

detailedDescription:
It was around 3.57am europe gmt time when looking to the general sky scenery something cought my eye aproaching from my right to my left pov.

it was very fast when compared to the size or a airplane, around 10x the size of a a320 following a domestic path, this when looking at the same supposed distance/height, a height where you can clearly distinguish the winglets/ tail lights. compared to a star which is only a small dot it would be roughly around 100x's the size, alot brighter!

regarding the brightness: this object was very bright, enough to made me turn my head and aknowledge it's presence. it made a small straight path horizontally, this while getting brighter. just imagine 1 (one) true white led of a flashlight, now put it in a dark room, make a small path with your hand holding the flashlight and you have a rough idea.

then, the most impressive thing about this sight, it pulsated for about 1 second, and it switched direction  in a rigid "v" shaped maneuver and it left a trail in the sky for about 1 second that quick disapeared while bliking the eye. the pulse was obvious, as also was the trail. it was basically like the entreprise warming up and going to warp speed in the well known movie. but alot more distance in this one.

no idea of the origin, who made etc. just clearly something not natural, like the shooting star that preceeded it around 4m. the type of light, movement nature (something not being propeled with fuel combustion engines, much more smoother), the relative velocity of the path in the sky and way it went to "warp" in a v shapped 180º change of direction.... just unbelieveble.

also, is anyone is closer to this it would be blind looking at it. this was  pure 7000k white, very homogeneous/soft but also solid light there!
description: Big led bright object with straigh path, then sudden warp speed type of path change.

detailedDescription: We were on our way home from working night shift, coming down the road to our home there is a hill where we saw something hovering. as we got closer it became much bigger . it was hovering just offside our road extremely low to the ground and when we got up too it our car was almost underneath it. we turnd the car off and jumped out and stood almost directly underneath it just staring up . it was around 5 am, we live in the countryside and there was no noise to be heard at all. pure silence. as we looked at it , it seemed to make a jumbo 747 look like a baby plane in comparison. it was a dark or black triangle and had 3 white rectangular panels of light under it so from where we looked at it , there was one rectangle above and two underneath all horizontal. the light was all evenly bright, no fluttering or movement of it. we stared at it for about 15 minutes looking at eachother like now what. then very suddnely it changed direction and zipped of diagonally to the east and dissappeard within seconds and without a sound. my husband still refuses to think it could be from another planet but he cannot refuse to admit what he saw. however 2 nights prior to this sighting i got up in the middle of the night to get a glass of water. when i went to the kitchen window i saw an object off to the east with colored lights (red, yellow, green) and it was doing manouvers like movine up , down, to the side and stopping each time. i could not see that well so went to get my binoculars. i could see much better but it was at quite a distance. i observed this strange movement until it dissapeard. i feel lucky to have witnessed these events. whether alien or earthly they were a sight to see.
description: Huge, silent triangle with 3 large rectangular light panels on the bottom of it

detailedDescription:
my wife and i were sitting on our balcony in albir, spain on sunday may 20, 2012 just after 9 pm. the skies were clear and there was no wind. i watched a bright object coming from the mountains on what i would guess  2-3 miles altitude. sometimes it was moving from left to right, slowly and most of the time it was almost still/not moving.
after a couple of minutes it started to move east (towards us) and after a minute or two it took off almost straight up and it looked like it accelerated to enormous speed  instantly and it went smaller and smaller and disappeared in about 3 seconds.
we can not tell the size of this as we do not know the altitude. the colour as we saw it was almost glowing (red /orange) and the light was consistent.
it took off at a small angle so we had some kind of speed impression as opposed to just leaving us in a straight line.
i have never believed in this before and i do not know if i do now but this is the most inexplicable thing i have ever seen.

(i only have access to limited software.) i am the original owner of the photo and is therefore my copyright.

detailedDescription:
I was fishing with my brother on the great river guadiana in badajoz spain on thursday 9th june 2011.
it was a wonderful sunny day only a couple of whispy clouds in sky. it was around 4pm and i was becoming a bit tired and thinking of packing up when i lazily lay back and rested enjoying the sunshine. i was staring straight up, i suppose 90 degrees to horizon.
 i must have lay like that for five minuets or so when from behind me and directly into my field of vision a clear black disc shape moved quite rapidly across the sky along the line of the river. my imidiate thought was wtf is that!!?? 
as noted above it was roughly asprin sized.
 i called to my brother who was engrossed in his fishing to look pointing at it. 
it took me quite by surprise, i sat up  as it moved down the river and towards the horizon.
 as it was sunny there was some glare off the water and my eyes took a moment to readjust i picked it up again and pointed to it but my brother only saw some birds down river and suggested that was what it was.
i just put it to the back of my mind for a while but i keep thinking about it and what it could have been.
 i dont remember seeing aircraft in the area at all that day. although there were lots of birds on the river.
 if it was a bird that is the first and fastest disc shaped bird i have ever seen!
description: Clear disc shape moving across clear blue sky badajoz spain

the following days i was searching in press for some report, but i cant find nothing.

that'''s all about this observation.

detailedDescription:
The night started off with a phone call from the security company that has sensors installed at my grandmas house. they told us that someone was trying to break in as one of the sensors had gone off. 
bear in mind that my grandmas house is literally two streets away from my parents my father, my grandma and i hop in my dads car baseball bat in hand to drive round and see what was going on.

driving up camino cerro del molino reaching the top of the hill i opened the window lit a cigarette and stuck my head out the window. then is when i saw the crafts triangular shape through the trees with lights on the underside. i screamed at my dad to stop the car and then he saw it coming overhead. we all got out of the car and stared at the triangular craft that at that moment was barely moving, i would dare say hovering overhead. we stood in the road for about a minute without saying anything. it was like seeing a flying football pitch in size. the craft didnt make a sound and the white lights on the outside didn't pulsate. it was like time stood still. the craft on the outside was black and smooth but its silhouette stood out against the night sky. 
it started moving off slowly in the same direction it was going and accelerated away quickly. 

we got back in the car shocked at what we had seen. we didn't say a word until we got back home after checking all was ok at grandmas house. 

this topic comes up always at christmas and family dinners but has never been officially reported.
description: Silent triangular craft at treetop level speed away

detailedDescription: I was sitting in a second seat next to a window, aft of the wing, on the starboard side. our flight had begun its landing approach/descent thus my estimate of 20,000ft is based on the approximate duration of descent. i looked out the window, something i seldom do, and i noticed what i assumed was an shiny aircraft. it struck me as curious. because it appeared significantly closer than any other aircraft seen on any previous flight. as i continued to look at it, i then noticed it was trailing black smoke. by that i don't mean black smoke that appears as grey engine exhaust. i mean dense , black, opaque smoke being left as a black trail behind the craft. the craft had just begun emitting the trail when i noticed it because although it continued the black emission the entire time i saw it, there was only a very short trail when i first viewed it.  as i looked at the craft, i realized that i really couldn't say with certainty that it was in fact a plane i had just assumed that it was on first glance. when i first saw it, the craft was below my plane and was quickly climbing at what i guess to be at least a 45 degree angle. because it was climbing at such an acute angle, i was able to have a better idea about its speed as compared to what i might have guessed if we were passing in opposite directions at the same altitude. i can't say with certainty that it was flying at an unimaginable speed but it was an extremely fast climb. concerning the crafts color, because i expected to see a plane i thought it had a silvery surface that was reflecting light but all i can say with certainty was that it was "bright white".  i am certain the pilots my airplane also saw the craft.
description: Seen from a commercial aircraft on flight from bristol, england to malaga spain
